snippet: Florida guard KeVaughn Allen had a triumphant return to Arkansas, where he played high school ball, scoring 21 points as the No. 25 Gators beat the Razorbacks 81-72 on Thursday night in the Southeastern Conference opener for both teams....
lead_paragraph: Florida guard KeVaughn Allen had a triumphant return to Arkansas, where he played high school ball, scoring 21 points as the No. 25 Gators beat the Razorbacks 81-72 on Thursday night in the Southeastern Conference opener for both teams.

headline.main: Happy Homecoming: Allen Leads No. 25 Florida Over Arkansas
headline.print_headline: Happy Homecoming: Allen Leads No. 25 Florida Over Arkansas
